231
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:06,008
- Fishermen don't like biologists.
- I know that.

232
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:11,491
- But I'm only the deck hand.
- Okay ...

233
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:16,561
- And I happen to like biologists.
- I see.

234
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:20,924
Especially when they look
as cute as you.

235
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:24,289
- And I thought ...
- Now, Lars!

236
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:34,405
- You probably find this hilarious.
- Not at all.

237
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:53,171
Drink some of this. Tiny gulps.

238
00:27:53,360 --> 00:27:58,161
I found some patches.
I don't know if they can expire.

239
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:00,328
It goes behind the ear.

240
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:05,684
You might need
to pull your hair away.

241
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:18,447
There. And don't sit in here.
Go outside in the fresh air.

242
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:21,484
And keep your eye on the horizon.

243
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:29,766
You'll be fine.
Do you want to come outside?

244
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,082
- Thank you.
- What about that?

245
00:28:46,280 --> 00:28:49,762
Just leave it. I'll be back.

246
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:53,123
- Thank you!
- You're welcome.

247
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:56,449
- Do you want some fish?
- Sure.

248
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:59,843
Lars, can you put them in a bag?

249
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:04,125
- How many do you want?
- Just a couple.

250
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:09,167
- Just use flour and butter.
- How much do you want?

251
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:15,129
- For you, 500 kroner.
- That's an illegal sale.

252
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:17,766
Someone's feeling all better.

253
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:22,045
Okay, so they're for free.
But the bag is 100 kroner.

254
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:25,011
See you.

255
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:02,608
- You're here?
- Yes.

256
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:06,481
- Hello, Kesse. The usual?
- Yes, please.

257
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:11,089
- What about the plaice?
- I'm afraid I burnt them.

258
00:30:11,320 --> 00:30:15,450
Don't say that out loud.
This town will have your head.

259
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:20,601
- I just can't multitask.
- So how long are you here for?

260
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:24,401
A couple of months for now.
It might get extended.

261
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:28,565
I thought someone like you
would hurry back to Copenhagen.

262
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:30,882
- Someone like me?
- Yes.

263
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:42,842
Would you like
to show me around some day?

264
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:47,682
- Like some sod of tour guide?
- Yes.

265
00:30:47,840 --> 00:30:52,129
Did you hear that, Pia?
A tour guide. What do you think?

266
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:55,449
You'll scare off
the rest of the tourists.

267
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,728
You don't have to do it.

268
00:30:57,920 --> 00:31:01,970
I should be able to spare
the 15 minutes that'll take.

269
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,362
How about Sunday?

270
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:08,849
- So there you go.
- Thanks. Sure.

271
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:14,201
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

272
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,687
Goodbye, Kesse.

273
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:27,004
Come in!

274
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:31,088
- Hi!
- Hello.

275
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:34,682
I'll be there in a second.
Come on in.

276
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:39,090
- I'll just wait here.
- No, come on in.

277
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:28,651
- Thanks for this. It's nice of you.
- Don't mention it.

278
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:36,850
I can start by showing you
one of our greatest sights.

279
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:40,203
This roundabout.
We're very proud of it.

280
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:45,645
Yes ... it's very nice.

281
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:50,841
- There's only one way in and out.
- That can't be true.

282
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:56,809
- I'll show you.
- That is so stupid. Go round again.

283
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:03,724
- One more? Okay, let's do it.
- Yes.

284
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:09,927
There's a bunker in the middle.
I don't know why.

285
00:33:10,120 --> 00:33:13,010
- It's nuts.
- Crazy.

286
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:17,967
- One more time?
- No, let's go.

287
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:22,560
Did you always
want to be a fisherman?

288
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:28,722
My dad and granddad were fishermen
so it was kind of expected.

289
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:41,561
Wow! Oh my God.

290
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:47,409
This is so cool.

291
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:50,649
- It's not like Copenhagen.
- No.

292
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:54,731
- Actually I've never been there.
- Never?

293
00:33:54,960 --> 00:34:01,445
I was one week in Tenerife
about 15 years ago. But that's it.

294
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:04,843
- You're a real adventurer.
- Yes.

295
00:34:07,080 --> 00:34:10,766
- You have to see Copenhagen.
- Really?

296
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:13,281
Maybe you're right.

297
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:18,884
- I think I'd get lost.
- I'll show you around.

298
00:34:19,040 --> 00:34:24,968
- Then maybe I should go some day.
- That's a deal.

299
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:33,241
- Oh my God.
- Yup.

300
00:34:40,640 --> 00:34:44,611
Where's the open sign?
I hope they're not closed.

301
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:53,925
That's too bad.
I wanted to take you up there.

302
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:57,966
Why are they closed
when the weather is so nice?

303
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:03,163
I think we can get in here.

304
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:08,605
- Don't do that.
- Relax. I'll try and get in.

305
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:11,491
Do you want to get in trouble?

306
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:20,641
How long have you and Lars
been fishing together?

307
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:23,844
A long time.

308
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:27,647
- He's a funny character.
- Aren't we all more or less?

309
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:31,003
Yes, I guess so.

310
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:34,010
Lars is a good guy.
He's had a rough life.

311
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:41,922
His dad Gunnar and my dad were
fishing partners for many years.

312
00:35:42,120 --> 00:35:47,331
One night we'd been out all night.
We were going for the last catch.

313
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:52,321
Gunnar got caught in the net.
There was nothing we could do.

314
00:35:55,120 --> 00:35:59,125
Lars was just 13 or 14 years old.

315
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:03,689
For a few years
he had trouble readjusting.

316
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:07,965
Then his mum asked me
if I could take him on the boat.

317
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:10,128
He's been with me ever since.

318
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:17,770
So he's an okay guy.

319
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:30,120
- There we go.
- Thank you.

320
00:36:35,680 --> 00:36:38,047
- Bye.
- Bye.

321
00:36:47,520 --> 00:36:51,491
- Hello, Pia.
- The usual?

322
00:36:58,960 --> 00:37:04,091
- No, wait. I'll try something new.
- Really?

323
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:08,529
- Which one do you want then?
- What's a Hawaii mix?

324
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:13,123
Sausages and fries with pineapple.
And with curry.

325
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:18,008
- It's good.
- Then get me one of those.

326
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:26,771
- Do you believe in clean slates?
- What do mean?

327
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:32,325
I don't know.
I'm just talking rubbish.

328
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:42,570
You don't get how serious this is.
A bonus is just a drop in the ocean.

329
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:45,445
It's a step in the right direction.

330
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:48,291
Will you take a biologist
with you every month?

331
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:51,370
You need to look
at the operations and costs.

332
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:57,966
Do you still have that deck hand on
fixed wages? No one else does that.

333
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:03,041
- I gave you a chance.
- I found the solution. More quotas.

334
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:08,007
More quotas? You need to
cut down on the costs and optimize.

335
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:13,730
Then go fish yourself, wise ass!
7 years ago I could easily get a loan.

336
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:18,403
You told me to buy the cod quotas.
I come here with a solution.

337
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:22,844
The least you can do is help me.
The house is my collateral.

338
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:29,042
- Did you find the quotas?
- I have an offer.

339
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:32,210
- At a good price?
- It's okay.

340
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:36,206
It's a temporary overdraft.
And I need to approve them.

341
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:40,081
- You have to cut down the costs.
- Wherever possible.

342
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:42,208
You know what I mean.

343
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:58,408
- Lars. We need to talk.
- Yes.

344
00:38:58,600 --> 00:39:04,448
- I'm sorry but I have to fire you.
- Shut up.

345
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:08,850
- I can't afford you anymore.
- Everything is okay.

346
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:13,688
- Everything is going to hell.
- We're catching fish. It's all good.

347
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:18,402
No. Listen to me.
I wouldn't just say this.

348
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:21,962
I might be able
to take you on again at some point.

349
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:27,291
What am I supposed to do then?
There are no other jobs out there.

350
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:30,927
- I was always with you.
- I don't want this either.

351
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:34,926
- I just can't help you right now.
- You never did!

352
00:39:35,120 --> 00:39:37,600
Don't do this, Lars. Lars!

353
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:41,560
I get why Kirsten left you.
You're worthless!

354
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:54,251
- Morning!
- Morning.

355
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:57,171
Can you take this? Thanks.

356
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:08,046
- Can you let go the moorings?
- Is Lars not coming? Is he ill?

357
00:40:08,240 --> 00:40:10,561
Yes.

358
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:14,685
- Let go the moorings and let's go.
- Yes.

359
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:50,931
- Do you need help?
- Grab a hold here.

360
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:54,363
Grab a good hold.
I'll count to three.

361
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:57,962
One, two, three! One more time.

362
00:40:58,160 --> 00:41:02,802
One, two, three! There!

363
00:41:08,200 --> 00:41:11,886
I couldn't have done that alone.
Now loosen the line.

364
00:41:12,080 --> 00:41:15,129
Watch out for the flood.

365
00:41:18,400 --> 00:41:21,529
Come on now. Pull!
You can do this. Yes.

366
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:36,403
So that was it then. You don't have
to go out to sea for a long time now.

367
00:41:36,640 --> 00:41:41,168
- It was a nice experience.
- I'm glad you think that.

368
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:52,051
I hope you got the data you need.

369
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:57,286
If not, you can come with me again.
We can arrange that.

370
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:38,163
<i>You bastard! I need to talk to you!
Kesse!</i>

371
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:44,450
- What the hell are you doing?
- Shut up! We need to talk!

372
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:47,849
Go home and sleep it off.

373
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:51,328
- Stop that!
- I want to talk to you!

374
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:55,645
I don't want to talk to you
when you're drunk. You know that.

375
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:58,525
- Stop that, damn it!
- We need to talk!

376
00:42:58,720 --> 00:43:03,248
- What do you want to say?
- You're a bastard.

377
00:43:03,440 --> 00:43:09,209
Is that all?
Damn it! Stop that! Lars.

378
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:14,168
Stop it. Come here. Don't.

379
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:17,330
Go away!

380
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:21,408
Don't!

381
00:43:21,560 --> 00:43:25,007
- Go home!
- Bastard.

382
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:29,729
Go home.

383
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:39,085
Can I get a beer?

384
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:46,089
- Thanks.
- Katrine ...

385
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:52,123
- Give me 3 beers. What's up?
- What's up with what?

386
00:43:52,280 --> 00:43:55,602
What's it like
taking a biologist with you?

387
00:43:55,840 --> 00:44:00,402
- It's okay.
- You told us to not do it.

388
00:44:00,640 --> 00:44:03,564
- Did I?
- Yes. But you did.

389
00:44:03,720 --> 00:44:07,486
- Even on your spare time.
- You people talk a lot.

390
00:44:07,640 --> 00:44:11,440
- Don't get things mixed up.
- Did you want anything else?

391
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:14,325
I'm just saying.

392
00:44:31,480 --> 00:44:33,528
- Hello, Kesse.
- Hello, Carsten.

393
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:37,361
Do you still have those quotas?

394
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:42,851
- Wait. Can you hear that? Listen.
- What?

395
00:44:43,040 --> 00:44:48,206
- It's the tune. It's changed.
- Funny. Do you want to sell or not?

396
00:44:48,400 --> 00:44:51,847
- How many do you need?
- Your 60 tons of plaice.

397
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:55,362
You'll be busy on that wee boat.

398
00:44:55,520 --> 00:45:01,209
- How much do you want for them?
- For you, 4.5 kroner per kilo.

399
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:04,364
You must be crazy.

400
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:09,361
- I'll pay 1.5 kroner per kilo.
- This isn't a gift shop.

401
00:45:09,560 --> 00:45:12,291
- 2.5 then?
- No.

402
00:45:12,480 --> 00:45:15,609
- 2.5. Come on.
- No.

403
00:45:17,680 --> 00:45:20,570
3 then. That's a good offer.

404
00:45:20,760 --> 00:45:25,209
- That's 180.000 in your pocket.
- Why should I lose money on you?

405
00:45:25,360 --> 00:45:29,570
- Come on.
- No. I'll talk to you later.

406
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:52,328
- Now what?
- I have another suggestion.

407
00:45:52,520 --> 00:45:59,369
Give me the quotas for 1.5 per kilo
and I'll bring in extras for you.

408
00:45:59,560 --> 00:46:05,010
- What are you talking about?
- I know how you got that car.

409
00:46:22,160 --> 00:46:26,882
- Is that biologist still with you?
- No.

410
00:46:27,080 --> 00:46:31,563
Give me a couple of days.
I'll see if can work something out.

411
00:46:34,880 --> 00:46:38,248
Thanks.

412
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:49,922
It's too risky.
It's not the 80's anymore.

413
00:46:50,120 --> 00:46:52,805
There are more inspectors
than fishermen.

414
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:56,049
- I'll lose it all.
- It's a slippery slope.

415
00:46:56,240 --> 00:47:01,246
- You'll end up in Carsten's pocket.
- I don't want to talk about it!

416
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:07,049
You just want me to shut down
and rot to death at the fish factory.

417
00:47:14,240 --> 00:47:17,050
His name is Preben.
This is his number.

418
00:47:17,240 --> 00:47:23,088
Call him when you bring extras in.
He'll come down and get it.

419
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:27,644
- Is he an okay guy?
- Sure. He's done this for years.

420
00:47:27,840 --> 00:47:32,402
- And he's never been caught?
- No.

421
00:47:32,600 --> 00:47:38,721
He'll pay you in cash.
Then we'll settle our account.

422
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:43,323
I have to say
that this surprised me.

423
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:46,729
- What?
- This. You.

424
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:52,006
You were always against
illegal fishing. You were a saint.

425
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:56,802
Was it all just hot air?

426
00:47:56,960 --> 00:48:00,362
This is not something I'll brag about.

427
00:48:04,640 --> 00:48:07,086
See you, Kesse.

428
00:48:15,720 --> 00:48:20,123
- Hello, Inga.
- Hello, Kesse. What do you want?

429
00:48:20,320 --> 00:48:25,804
- Is Lars here?
- Yes. Lars. Lars!

430
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:30,210
- All right, all right. Calm down.
- Hello, Lars.

431
00:48:32,720 --> 00:48:35,803
- What do you want?
- I can take you back on.

432
00:48:37,200 --> 00:48:39,851
- What happened?
- Do you want to come?

433
00:48:40,080 --> 00:48:43,721
- Yes. Of course.
- See you tomorrow at 4 then.

434
00:48:46,280 --> 00:48:48,601
Aye aye, captain.

435
00:48:48,800 --> 00:48:51,929
- Do you want a cup of coffee?
- No, thanks.

436
00:48:52,120 --> 00:48:58,127
I need to go. Take care.

437
00:48:58,360 --> 00:49:00,931
- See you, Kesse!
- Yes.

438
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:19,404
- Was that all?
- Yes. 8 cod crates.

439
00:49:25,800 --> 00:49:29,486
Put them over here and cover them.

440
00:49:32,520 --> 00:49:36,491
- Do you have the fishing report?
- Yes. Here you go.

441
00:49:36,720 --> 00:49:39,963
- See you tomorrow.
- Yes. Thanks.

442
00:49:49,680 --> 00:49:53,127
- What do we do now?
- We sail back.

443
00:49:53,320 --> 00:49:55,721
Preben will pick up the rest there.

444
00:50:31,520 --> 00:50:34,205
Are you Preben?
Can you park over here?

445
00:50:34,400 --> 00:50:38,769
- Sure. Let's have a look at it.
- Yes.

446
00:51:05,560 --> 00:51:08,166
- So that was it.
- Yes.

447
00:51:08,360 --> 00:51:11,921
- So I'll see you next week.
- We'll see.

448
00:51:12,120 --> 00:51:16,205
Call me when you have something.

449
00:51:16,400 --> 00:51:21,088
- So was everything okay?
- Yes. No problems.

450
00:51:21,320 --> 00:51:25,086
- Let's see.
- I hope they're all there.

451
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:28,409
- Everything looks okay.
- Good.

452
00:51:30,280 --> 00:51:32,851
Nothing to worry about then.

453
00:51:35,600 --> 00:51:38,080
There.

454
00:51:39,800 --> 00:51:42,690
- Do you want a beer?
- No, thanks.

455
00:51:42,880 --> 00:51:45,884
- See you next week.
- Yes.

456
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:08,086
- Hello.
- Hi. What are you doing here?

457
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:12,689
- Will you help me with these?
- Sure.

458
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:16,487
- Did you pay for them?
- No.

459
00:52:19,080 --> 00:52:22,846
- Can I come in?
- Yes, of course.

460
00:52:23,000 --> 00:52:26,402
Then you cut it along the spine.

461
00:52:26,640 --> 00:52:30,645
Then we remove this bone.
It's not nice to eat that.

